    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">13. Do Not Track And Similar Signals</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700">Some browsers offer Do Not Track or similar privacy signals. There is no single universal standard for how all websites must respond to these signals in every jurisdiction. Where technically practical and legally relevant, we evaluate privacy signals together with consent and opt out controls. We focus on practical compliance: ensuring readers can make meaningful choices and that non essential tracking is not silently forced where consent is expected.</p>

